---
name: scljet-sql-case
description: SclJet SQL CASE expression (searched + simple) and comparison-as-value; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL CASE expression

`CASE WHEN cond THEN r [WHEN …]* [ELSE r] END` (searched form) and `CASE operand WHEN v THEN r … END`
(simple form). A comparison is itself an expression yielding `1`/`0`/NULL (as in sqlite), so `WHEN
salary > 200` works and `SELECT salary > 200` returns 0/1. CASE composes with arithmetic (`THEN
salary*2`), has no ELSE → NULL, and works in `WHERE`. Every result is byte-identical to reference
sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, salary INTEGER, dept INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(100L), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(250L), SqlInteger(20L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat"), SqlInteger(300L), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(150L), SqlInteger(30L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, CASE WHEN salary >= 250 THEN 'high' WHEN salary >= 150 THEN 'mid' ELSE 'low' END FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT id, CASE dept WHEN 10 THEN 'eng' WHEN 20 THEN 'sales' ELSE 'other' END FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT id, CASE WHEN salary > 200 THEN 'big' END FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT id, CASE WHEN dept = 10 THEN salary * 2 ELSE salary END FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT id, salary > 200 FROM emp")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE CASE WHEN dept = 10 THEN salary > 200 ELSE salary > 100 END")
```
